3:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","IMX","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX funding rates often diverge significantly during gaming sector rallies and NFT market cycles, creating arbitrage opportunities. The token's correlation with Ethereum gas fees and gaming platform adoption drives unique funding dynamics not seen in traditional DeFi tokens."}]]}]
4:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX funding rates on dYdX have shown strong correlation with gaming sector sentiment and NFT market cycles. During Q4 2023 gaming rallies, funding rates consistently traded at +0.15% to +0.25% hourly due to strong long positioning. The token exhibits seasonal patterns around major game launches and partnership announcements. Gaming tokens typically see funding spikes during weekend trading when retail interest peaks in NFT markets."}]]}]
5:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The 1-hour funding intervals create frequent arbitrage windows, especially during high volatility periods in the gaming sector. Traders can capitalize on funding rate differentials between dYdX and centralized exchanges like Binance or OKX which use 8-hour cycles. Cross-exchange arbitrage becomes particularly profitable when IMX experiences gaming-specific news events. The decentralized nature of dYdX allows for permissionless arbitrage without KYC restrictions common on CEXs."}]]}]
6:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"IMX exhibits higher volatility than major cryptocurrencies due to its gaming sector exposure and smaller market cap. The Cosmos appchain migration introduced additional smart contract risks not present in the original StarkEx implementation. Gaming token funding rates can remain elevated for extended periods during sector rotations, increasing carry costs for short positions. Lower liquidity compared to major pairs can lead to wider bid-ask spreads during volatile funding periods."}]]}]
7:["$","$Lc",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are IMX funding payments settled on dYdX?","answer":"IMX funding payments are settled every hour on dYdX, at the top of each hour. This is significantly more frequent than the 8-hour cycles used by most centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What drives IMX funding rate volatility on dYdX?","answer":"IMX funding rates are primarily driven by gaming sector sentiment, NFT market cycles, and major partnership announcements from Immutable. Weekend trading often sees increased retail participation in gaming tokens."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage IMX funding rates between dYdX and other exchanges?","answer":"Yes, the 1-hour vs 8-hour funding cycle difference creates arbitrage opportunities. However, consider gas costs, liquidity differences, and the risks of holding positions across multiple platforms."},{"question":"What are the main risks of trading IMX perpetuals on dYdX?","answer":"Key risks include higher volatility due to gaming sector exposure, potential smart contract risks from the Cosmos appchain migration, and lower liquidity compared to major trading pairs."}]}]
